It chronicles the life of Gabriela Brimmer, Mexican writer and disability rights activist. Gaby Brimmer, the child of Austrian refugees living in Mexico, is born with cerebral palsy. Though her body is completely paralyzed, her mind is unaffected, and she is able to become a college graduate and an acclaimed author.
